==English==
===Noun===
'''procedure''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''procedures''')

#A [[particular]] [[method]] for [[performing]] a [[task]].
#A [[series]] of small tasks taken to [[accomplish]] an [[end]].
#(''uncountable'') The [[set]] of [[established]] [[form]]s or methods of an [[organized]] [[body]] for accomplishing a certain task or tasks.
#:''Ensure that you follow procedure when accessing customers' personal information.''
#(''computing'') A [[subroutine]] or [[function]] [[code]]d to perform a specific task.

====Synonyms====
*(''method''): [[algorithm]], [[method]], [[process]], [[routine]]
*(''set of established forms or methods of an organized body''): [[protocol]]
*(''computing''): [[function]], [[routine]], [[subroutine]] (''although some of these have slightly differing meanings in some programming languages'')

